('/works/OL18188824W', 'Sherlock Holmes (Adventures of Sherlock Holmes / M', '- [Adventures of Sherlock Holmes](https://openlibrary.org/works/OL262421W/The_Adventures_of_Sherlock_Holmes)\r\n[Scandal in Bohemia](https://openlibrary.org/works/OL14930611W/A_Scandal_in_Bohemia)\r\n[Red-headed League](https://openlibrary.org/works/OL14930336W/The_Red-Headed_League)\r\n[Case of Identity](https://openlibrary.org/works/OL14929939W/A_Case_of_Identity)\r\n[Boscombe Valley Mystery](https://openlibrary.org/works/OL18495288W/The_Boscombe_Valley_Mystery)\r\n[Five Orange Pips](https://openlibrary', 'Arthur Conan Doyle', 'OL36631022M', 20.99),
('/works/OL1822313W', 'Tuesdays with Morrie', 'Tuesdays with Morrie is a memoir by American author Mitch Albom about a series of visits Albom made to his former sociology professor Morrie Schwartz, as Schwartz gradually dies of ALS. The book topped the New York Times Non-Fiction Best-Sellers List for 23 combined weeks in 2000, and remained on the New York Times best-selling list for more than four years after. In 2006, Tuesdays with Morrie was the bestselling memoir of all time.', 'Mitch Albom', 'OL36671550M', 60.99),
