('/works/OL88640W', 'The Stones of Venice', 'The Stones of Venice is a three-volume treatise on Venetian art and architecture by English art historian John Ruskin, first published from 1851 to 1853.\r\n\r\nThe Stones of Venice examines Venetian architecture in detail, describing for example over eighty churches. Ruskin discusses architecture of Venice\'s Byzantine, Gothic, and Renaissance periods, and provides a general history of the city.', 'John Ruskin', 'OL24197185M', 6.99),
