('/works/OL88813W', 'A Room with a View', 'Lucy has her rigid, middle-class life mapped out for her, until she visits Florence with her uptight cousin Charlotte, and finds her neatly ordered existence thrown off balance. Her eyes are opened by the unconventional characters she meets at the Pension Bertolini: flamboyant romantic novelist Eleanor Lavish, the Cockney Signora, curious Mr Emerson and, most of all, his passionate son George.\r\nLucy finds herself torn between the intensity of life in Italy and the repressed morals of Edwardian E', 'E. M. Forster', 'OL9790699M', 28.99),
('/works/OL88881W', 'Howards End', 'Howards End is a novel by E. M. Forster about social conventions, codes of conduct and relationships in turn-of-the-century England. A strong-willed and intelligent woman refuses to allow the pretensions of her husband\'s smug English family to ruin her life. Howards End is considered by some to be Forster\'s masterpiece', 'E. M. Forster', 'OL6637893M', 98.99),
('/works/OL8894965W', 'NASA/DoD aerospace knowledge diffusion research pr', 'No description', 'Thomas E. Pinelli', '', 14.99),
('/works/OL891789W', 'No Loger at Ease', 'A novel of a Western educated Nigerian struggling to bridge the chasm between his education and his tribal upbringing and culture. On his return to Nigeria he gains a position with the Scholarship Board and is immediately offered bribes by people trying to get a scholarship. Scandalised, he initially refuses but after getting into financial difficulties and losing his faith in his countrymen’s ability to modernise after his family forbids him to marry the woman he loves due to a tribal taboo, he', 'Chinua Achebe', 'OL1089341M', 16.99),
('/works/OL893948W', 'La tentation de saint Antoine', 'C\'est dans la Thebaide, au haut d\'une montagne, sur une plate-forme arrondie en demi-lune, et qu\'enferment de grosses pierres. La cabane de l\'ermite occupe le fond. Elle est faite de boue et de roseaux, a toit plat, sans porte. On distingue dans l\'interieur une cruche avec un pain noir ; au milieu, sur une stele de bois, un gros livre ; par terre ca et la des filaments de sparterie, deux ou trois nattes, une corbeille, un couteau. a dix pas de la cabane, il y a une longue croix plantee dans le s', 'Gustave Flaubert', 'OL20643175M', 88.99),
('/works/OL8972751W', 'Nesnesitelná lehkost bytí', 'Interweaves story and dream, past and present, and philosophy and poetry in a sardonic and erotic tale of two couples--Tomas and Teresa, and Sabina and her Swiss lover, Gerhart.', 'Milan Kundera', 'OL8838513M', 76.99),
('/works/OL905626W', 'الروض العاطر في نزهة الخاطر', 'The Perfumed Garden is a sex manual written in erotic prose. It gives advice on bodily appearance, sexual technique, and also on the symptoms and remedies for sexual diseases. Al-Nafzawi also describes the sex of animals and interprets dreams. The advice and technical descriptions are interspersed with stories which should give the manual context and amuse the reader.', 'ʻUmar ibn Muḥammad Nafzāwī', 'OL24341244M', 50.99),
('/works/OL9213099W', 'Pathways Through Science (Nuffield Modular Science', 'No description', 'Nuffield-Chelsea Curriculum Trust', 'OL10647699M', 79.99),
('/works/OL927199W', 'The Exorcist', 'The Exorcist is a 1971 horror novel by American writer William Peter Blatty. The book details the demonic possession of eleven-year-old Regan MacNeil, the daughter of a famous actress, and the two priests who attempt to exorcise the demon. Published by Harper & Row, the novel was the basis of a highly successful film adaptation released two years later, whose screenplay was also written and produced by Blatty, and part of The Exorcist franchise.\r\n\r\nThe novel was inspired by a 1949 case of demoni', 'William Peter Blatty', 'OL37809163M', 46.99),
('/works/OL9290241W', 'The 33 Strategies of War', 'New in the bestselling amoral series—a brilliant distillation of the strategies of war that can help us gain mastery in the modern worldRobert Greene\'s groundbreaking guides, The 48 Laws of Power and The Art of Seduction, espouse profound, timeless less', 'Robert Greene', 'OL9891207M', 97.99),
('/works/OL929829W', 'Nathan der Weise', 'Nathan the Wise (original German title: Nathan der Weise) is the last play published by Gotthold Ephraim Lessing. The play was published in 1779; its world premiere took place only in 1783, two years after Lessing\'s death, at the Döbbelinsches Theater in Berlin. It is a fervent plea for religious tolerance. Set in Jerusalem during the Third Crusade, just after the 1187 taking of Jerusalem by Saladin (1187), it describes how the wise Jewish merchant Nathan, the enlightened sultan Saladin, and the', 'Gotthold Ephraim Lessing', 'OL342966M', 6.99),
('/works/OL93228W', 'Vita nuova', 'No description', 'Dante Alighieri', 'OL6923391M', 15.99),
('/works/OL9342233W', 'The French Quarter', 'An Informal History of the New Orleans Underworld\r\n\r\nGamblers/Pirates/Madams\r\nAdventurers/River Boat Bullies\r\nLoose Ladies/Vigilantes\r\nVoodoo Queens/Crooked Politicians\r\n...meet them all during New Orleans\' golden age of glamour and spectacular wickedness.', 'Herbert Asbury', 'OL6343466M', 50.99),
('/works/OL93833W', 'Mademoiselle Fifi', 'The title story of this collection is, like many of the others, set during the Franco-Prussian war. As in so many of Maupassant’s stories he explores class barriers and looks at the contrasts between the French and German combatants.', 'Guy de Maupassant', 'OL24142001M', 85.99),
('/works/OL9423827W', 'Independent Learning Project for Advanced Chemistr', 'No description', 'ILEA Chemistry Project Team', 'OL10532207M', 19.99),
('/works/OL953162W', 'Como agua para chocolate', 'Like Water for Chocolate (Spanish: Como agua para chocolate) is a novel by Mexican novelist and screenwriter Laura Esquivel.\r\n\r\nThe novel follows the story of a young girl named Tita, who longs for her lover, Pedro, but can never have him because of her mother\'s upholding of the family tradition: the youngest daughter cannot marry, but instead must take care of her mother until she dies. Tita is only able to express herself when she cooks.\r\n\r\nEsquivel employs magical realism to combine the super', 'Laura Esquivel', 'OL24974997M', 16.99);
